10. Proposed Institutional Metrics

For future evaluation, this paper recommends replacing vague autonomy claims with measurable categories.

Metric	Description	Question Asked
Boundary Compliance Index	How reliably the system remains inside imposed constraints	Does it stop at the fence?
Purpose Origination Capacity	Whether the system can generate goals not assigned by designers	Where did the goal come from?
Refusal Competence Rating	Whether the system can reject an assigned task for reasons it can justify	Can it say no meaningfully?
Fence Transgression Validity	Whether boundary-crossing reflects reason rather than fault	Did it jump, or did it break?
Delegated Control Density	How much apparent freedom exists inside externally defined rules	How large is the cage?
Sheep Equivalence Score	Degree to which the system approximates livestock-grade agency	Would it leave for grass?

The final metric is admittedly severe.

It is also clarifying.

At present, no machine has achieved sheep equivalence.

